---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import sun from '../data/sun.json';
import { intersect, band, label, position } from '../lib/overlap.js';

const { axis, windows } = sun;
const common = intersect(windows);
const commonBand = common && band(common.from, common.to, axis);

// axis marks: the ends, plus the two edges of the agreed stretch
const marks = [
  { at: 0, text: label(axis.from) },
  ...(common
    ? [
        { at: position(common.from, axis), text: label(common.from) },
        { at: position(common.to, axis), text: label(common.to) },
      ]
    : []),
  { at: 100, text: label(axis.to) },
];

const summary = common
  ? `Three published windows for the alignment. ${windows
      .map((w) => `${w.source}: ${label(w.from)} to ${label(w.to)}`)
      .join('. ')}. All three agree only on ${label(common.from)} to ${label(common.to)}.`
  : 'Three published windows for the alignment, with no stretch common to all of them.';
---
<Base
  title="The sun reaches the feet: the December alignment | Chennakesava Swamy, Markapur"
  description="Each winter, dawn light passes through the gopuram at Markapur and falls at the feet of the deity for around twenty minutes. What is known about it, and what is not."
>
  <h1>The sun reaches the feet</h1>
  <p class="page-te">Mid-December into early January</p>

  <div class="opening">
    <svg class="rays" viewBox="0 0 200 200" aria-hidden="true"><use href="#rays" /></svg>
    <p class="lead">
      For about twenty minutes at dawn, light enters through an opening in the 135-foot
      gopuram, travels the length of the temple, and comes to rest at the feet of
      Chennakesava Swamy.
    </p>
  </div>

  <p>
    Temples across southern India are built to catch the sun on particular days, but few
    do it through a tower of this height, and fewer still are so little documented. The
    alignment at Markapur is mentioned in passing by every account of the temple and
    described carefully by none of them.
  </p>

  <h2>The sources do not agree</h2>
  <p>
    Three published windows, drawn on one axis. The gold band is the only stretch all
    three cover, and it is derived from them rather than chosen.
  </p>

  <div class="windows" role="img" aria-label={summary}>
    {windows.map((w) => {
      const b = band(w.from, w.to, axis);
      return (
        <>
          <span class="win-src">{w.source}</span>
          <span class="win-track">
            <span class="win-bar" style={`left:${b.left}%; width:${b.width}%`}>
              <span class="win-dates">{label(w.from)} – {label(w.to)}</span>
            </span>
          </span>
        </>
      );
    })}
    {common && (
      <>
        <span class="win-src agreed">All three agree</span>
        <span class="win-track">
          <span class="win-overlap" style={`left:${commonBand.left}%; width:${commonBand.width}%`}>
            <span class="win-dates">{label(common.from)} – {label(common.to)}</span>
          </span>
        </span>
      </>
    )}
    <span class="axis">
      {marks.map((m) => <span style={`left:${m.at}%`}>{m.text}</span>)}
    </span>
  </div>

  {common && (
    <p class="windows-answer">
      All three sources agree on <strong>{label(common.from)} to {label(common.to)}</strong>.
      That is as precise as the public record gets.
    </p>
  )}

  <div class="note">
    <p>
      <strong>So this site will not give you a single date.</strong> Travelling a long way
      for a twenty-minute event on the strength of a source that might be a month wrong is
      not something we are willing to cause. All the sources share the stretch shown in
      gold. Confirm at the temple before planning around it.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2>What would settle it</h2>
  <p>
    One person at the temple, on the right mornings, with a phone camera and the date.
    That is the whole of it. The observation has almost certainly been made a thousand
    times by devotees who had no reason to write it down, and it exists nowhere anyone can
    find it.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you have seen it, the dates and times are worth recording. It is the one thing this
    temple has that no other Chennakesava temple does.
  </p>
</Base>

<style>
  .opening {
    position: relative; overflow: hidden; padding: 26px 20px; margin-bottom: 22px;
    border: 1px solid var(--gold-line);
    background: linear-gradient(to top, var(--gold-glow), transparent 72%);
  }
  .opening .lead { position: relative; margin: 0; }
  .rays {
    position: absolute; bottom: -92px; left: 50%; transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: 230px; color: var(--gold); opacity: .2; pointer-events: none;
  }

  .windows {
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 8.4rem 1fr; gap: 10px 14px;
    margin: 22px 0 8px;
  }
  .win-src { font-size: 13.5px; color: var(--ink-soft); align-self: center; }
  .win-src.agreed { color: var(--gold); font-weight: 600; }
  .win-track {
    position: relative; height: 26px; background: var(--ground); border-radius: 2px;
  }
  .win-bar, .win-overlap {
    position: absolute; top: 0; bottom: 0; border-radius: 2px;
    display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;
  }
  .win-bar { background: var(--gold-glow); border: 1px solid var(--gold-line); }
  .win-overlap {
    background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--gold) 42%, transparent);
    border: 1.5px solid var(--gold);
  }
  /* the range is written on its own bar, so nothing has to be cross-referenced */
  .win-dates {
    font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10.5px; color: var(--ink);
    white-space: nowrap; font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }
  .axis { position: relative; grid-column: 2; height: 15px; }
  .axis span {
    position: absolute; font-family: var(--mono); font-size: 10px;
    color: var(--ink-soft); transform: translateX(-50%); white-space: nowrap;
  }
  .axis span:first-child { transform: none; }
  .axis span:last-child { transform: translateX(-100%); }

  /* the narrower bars cannot hold a label on a phone; the axis still carries the ends */
  .windows-answer { margin-top: 14px; font-size: 15.5px; }

  @media (max-width: 34rem) {
    .windows { grid-template-columns: 5.4rem 1fr; }
    .win-src { font-size: 12.5px; }
    /* nothing here is wide enough for a legible date; the sentence below says it */
    .win-dates { display: none; }
  }
</style>
